      • isEventOverlapFreeIntoSchedule

        public boolean isEventOverlapFreeIntoSchedule(Event event,
                                              boolean forSwap)
        States if an event has any kind of overlapping into the schedule. This function is called before the calculation of possible paths for an event that could be added. Paths are not considered in this function because the addition of an event will cause the recalculation of involved paths.
        Parameters:
        event - event to be added.
        forSwap - indicates if the event is an existing and overlapping event that must be swapped into the schedule.
        Returns:
        true if the event has no overlapping with other events and its adding does not cause the impossibility to ensure minimum time for scheduled breaks; false otherwise.

      • isBreakOverlapFreeIntoSchedule

        public boolean isBreakOverlapFreeIntoSchedule(BreakEvent breakEvent,
                                              boolean forSwap)
        States if, in the actual schedule, the minimum amount of time can be ensured for a break event and if the break event has overlapping with other breaks. It is called when a breakEvent could be added into the schedule.
        Parameters:
        breakEvent - break to be added.
        forSwap - indicates if the break is an existing and overlapping event that must be swapped into the schedule.
        Returns:
        true if the break has no overlapping with other breaks and the schedule ensure the minimum amount of time for the break, false otherwise.

      • areEventsOverlapFree

        public boolean areEventsOverlapFree(GenericEvent event,
                                    GenericEvent scheduledEvent)
        States if two events are overlapping free without considering related-paths.
        Parameters:
        event - one of the two events to compare, the not scheduled one.
        scheduledEvent - one of the two events to compare, the scheduled one.
        Returns:
        true if the two events are not overlapping, false otherwise.

      • overlappingEventWithBreak

        public long overlappingEventWithBreak(Event event,
                                      BreakEvent breakEv)
        Calculates the amount of overlapping time between an event and a break event, eventually considering the path related to the event.
        Parameters:
        event - event of which calculate overlapping time.
        breakEv - break of which calculate overlapping time.
        Returns:
        the sum of the overlapping time between the two events and the overlapping time between the path and the break event.

      • getFeasiblePathCombinations

        public java.util.List<PathCombination> getFeasiblePathCombinations(Event event,
                                                                   java.util.List<Travel> previous,
                                                                   java.util.List<Travel> following)
        Defines, for each possible combination of previous-and-following path of an event, if it can be ensure the minimum amount of time for each scheduled break. This function is called after that all feasible previous and following paths are calculated.
        Parameters:
        event - the event of which the paths are related.
        previous - possible travels that don't overlap with previous event and respect user's preferences.
        following - possible travels that don't overlap with following event and respect user's preferences.
        Returns:
        all feasible combinations, according to the scheduled break events.

      • getFeasiblePathCombinationsLastEventCase

        private java.util.List<PathCombination> getFeasiblePathCombinationsLastEventCase(Event event,
                                                                                 java.util.List<Travel> previous)
        Defines, for each possible previous path of an event, if it can be ensure the minimum amount of time for each scheduled break. This function is called after that all feasible previous paths are calculated, when an event is the last of the schedule.
        Parameters:
        event - the event of which the paths are related.
        previous - possible travels that don't overlap with previous event and respect user's preferences.
        Returns:
        all feasible combinations, where the following path is null, according to the scheduled break events.

      • removeLongWalkingPath

        private java.util.List<PathCombination> removeLongWalkingPath(java.util.List<PathCombination> possiblePaths)
        Eliminates, if possible, all the solutions that have a travel component with a length greater than MAX_WALKING_LENGTH and BY_FOOT as travel mean. It is possible to eliminate this travels only if there exists at least one combination in the list passed as a parameter that doesn't contain "long walking paths".
        Parameters:
        possiblePaths - list of combinations of prev-foll path to analize.
        Returns:
        combinations in the list passed as a parameter with no "long walking paths" or the entire list if all the combinations contain at least one "long walking path".
